258
00:12:32,453 --> 00:12:34,319
Klein: Mm-hmm.

259
00:12:34,388 --> 00:12:36,054
Now the hard part.

260
00:12:36,123 --> 00:12:39,191
There's 30,000
American vrmmo players diving,

261
00:12:39,259 --> 00:12:41,794
and soon it could
go up to 100 thou.

262
00:12:41,862 --> 00:12:44,997
The human army's
just a bunch of targets to them.

263
00:12:45,065 --> 00:12:47,732
Lisbeth: What's stopping us from
doing what the hijackers did?

264
00:12:47,802 --> 00:12:51,336
We can post on the same
U.S. vrmmo sites, too.

265
00:12:51,405 --> 00:12:53,538
We'll tell the players
about the experiment

266
00:12:53,540 --> 00:12:56,408
and the fake beta.
I'm pretty sure they'll listen.

267
00:12:56,477 --> 00:12:58,210
Yui: At the center of it all
is a struggle

268
00:12:58,278 --> 00:13:01,013
for military secrets
between Japan and America.

269
00:13:01,081 --> 00:13:04,949
If we told anyone about that,
it would just make this worse.

270
00:13:04,951 --> 00:13:06,150
Agil: Mm-hmm.

271
00:13:06,152 --> 00:13:07,152
Silica: If we said
they'd be killing

272
00:13:07,221 --> 00:13:09,221
real people,
not avatars, maybe--

273
00:13:09,289 --> 00:13:10,955
oh, who am I kidding?

274
00:13:11,025 --> 00:13:12,224
( Klein scoffs )

275
00:13:12,292 --> 00:13:15,894
Well, I say we tear a page
out of their playbook.

276
00:13:15,962 --> 00:13:18,563
We'll post a notice
for the beta test ourselves.

277
00:13:18,565 --> 00:13:21,033
Then we get the rath guys
to hand out accounts,

278
00:13:21,101 --> 00:13:24,703
and I bet we could get 30,000
or 40,000 logged on, easy.

279
00:13:24,771 --> 00:13:27,840
Agil: That's a great idea, man,
but there's one problem.

280
00:13:27,908 --> 00:13:29,842
Klein: You gonna
tell me what that is?

281
00:13:29,910 --> 00:13:31,243
- Agil: The time.
- ( Klein gasps )

282
00:13:31,311 --> 00:13:34,513
Agil: Here in Japan,
it's 4:30 in the morning.

283
00:13:34,581 --> 00:13:37,516
Besides us, there's not
a whole lot of folks online.

284
00:13:37,584 --> 00:13:40,385
But in Los Angeles,
it's half past noon right now

285
00:13:40,454 --> 00:13:42,454
and 3:30 in New York.

286
00:13:42,523 --> 00:13:45,323
The U.S. has way more
active players online.

287
00:13:45,392 --> 00:13:46,925
( Klein groans )

288
00:13:46,993 --> 00:13:49,261
Yui: Agil is correct about that.

289
00:13:49,329 --> 00:13:52,464
We couldn't get the number
of players we need right now.

290
00:13:52,533 --> 00:13:54,867
It would be
way less than 10,000.

291
00:13:54,935 --> 00:13:58,070
Our accounts would be
the same level as the Americans,

292
00:13:58,138 --> 00:14:00,004
so we'd be evenly matched.

293
00:14:00,074 --> 00:14:01,940
Fighting all of them off
would be impossible.

294
00:14:02,008 --> 00:14:05,210
Lisbeth: But, like, maybe rath
has more god accounts

295
00:14:05,212 --> 00:14:06,411
like the one Asuna's using.

296
00:14:06,480 --> 00:14:08,480
We can't start from scratch.

297
00:14:08,549 --> 00:14:11,750
We'd need as much time as kirito
to level up enough.

298
00:14:11,818 --> 00:14:14,152
Klein: Crap. Game over, then.

299
00:14:14,221 --> 00:14:15,087
- Yui: No.
- ( Both gasp )

300
00:14:15,155 --> 00:14:17,956
Yui: There are strong accounts,

301
00:14:18,024 --> 00:14:21,093
both in terms of level
and in equipment.

302
00:14:21,161 --> 00:14:24,028
The Americans' default accounts
can't compare.

303
00:14:24,030 --> 00:14:26,765
Lisbeth: Really?
How do we get them?

304
00:14:26,833 --> 00:14:29,501
Yui: That's the best part.
The accounts are already yours.

305
00:14:29,570 --> 00:14:31,303
They're the ones
you're logged in with now.

306
00:14:31,371 --> 00:14:32,971
Lisbeth: Huh?

307
00:14:33,039 --> 00:14:34,639
Yui: You must convert them.

308
00:14:34,641 --> 00:14:36,508
If you do, then you

309
00:14:36,577 --> 00:14:40,112
and all the other vrmmo players
you recruit will start

310
00:14:40,180 --> 00:14:42,381
with stronger accounts
than the Americans.

311
00:14:42,449 --> 00:14:45,450
You're all leveled up already.
Just convert, and log in!

312
00:14:45,519 --> 00:14:48,186
Klein: Of course! Why didn't
any of us think of that?!

313
00:14:48,255 --> 00:14:53,325
Yui: Although I should mention
this plan involves some risk.

314
00:14:53,393 --> 00:14:55,194
( Crowd murmuring )

315
00:14:58,532 --> 00:14:59,932
Lisbeth: What i'm
about to tell you

316
00:15:00,000 --> 00:15:01,600
is not some kind of prank.

317
00:15:01,668 --> 00:15:04,336
There's a place
called the Underworld.

318
00:15:04,405 --> 00:15:07,071
It's a virtual world
based on the seed,

319
00:15:07,073 --> 00:15:09,141
made by Japanese researchers.

320
00:15:09,209 --> 00:15:11,810
As I stand here,
tens of thousands

321
00:15:11,878 --> 00:15:14,012
of American players
are logging in to it.

322
00:15:14,081 --> 00:15:16,348
They've been told it's a beta
for a hack-and-slash game

323
00:15:16,416 --> 00:15:18,951
and they can kill
anyone they come across.

324
00:15:19,019 --> 00:15:21,553
But the people
of the Underworld are real.

325
00:15:21,622 --> 00:15:23,421
They're not just npcs.

326
00:15:23,490 --> 00:15:25,157
They're true bottom-up a.I.S

327
00:15:25,225 --> 00:15:27,426
with feelings
and souls like us.

328
00:15:27,494 --> 00:15:29,227
We need your help
to protect them,

329
00:15:29,296 --> 00:15:30,963
but there's no time
to level up there.

330
00:15:31,031 --> 00:15:33,298
But if you convert
your character accounts

331
00:15:33,367 --> 00:15:36,100
to the Underworld,
we can save their people!

332
00:15:36,102 --> 00:15:37,836
( Crowd murmuring )

333
00:15:40,440 --> 00:15:42,307
Sakuya: I know you well,

334
00:15:42,376 --> 00:15:44,242
and I trust your intentions.

335
00:15:44,311 --> 00:15:46,178
You wouldn't have
called us so early

336
00:15:46,246 --> 00:15:48,180
just so you could play
a trick on us.

337
00:15:48,248 --> 00:15:51,650
And the fact kirito hasn't
logged on for over ten days

338
00:15:51,718 --> 00:15:55,520
suggests whatever is going on
is indeed serious.

339
00:15:55,522 --> 00:15:58,923
But a.I.S with human souls

340
00:15:58,993 --> 00:16:01,460
and the U.S. military
out to steal them,

341
00:16:01,528 --> 00:16:04,596
it all seems so far-fetched.

342
00:16:04,665 --> 00:16:07,332
Diving in would be
the only way to confirm it.

343
00:16:07,401 --> 00:16:11,203
In private, you told me
you had other concerns,

344
00:16:11,271 --> 00:16:14,939
that converting our accounts
would have risks.

345
00:16:15,009 --> 00:16:18,143
You should explain
what those are before we decide.

346
00:16:18,212 --> 00:16:19,478
Lisbeth: Sure.

347
00:16:19,546 --> 00:16:21,914
Here's what I know.

348
00:16:23,283 --> 00:16:26,084
The Underworld
isn't a vrmmo game.

349
00:16:26,152 --> 00:16:28,020
It's a simulated civilization,

350
00:16:28,088 --> 00:16:32,224
so you'll be faced with
a few issues once you dive in.

351
00:16:32,292 --> 00:16:35,293
The first one
is there's no user interface

352
00:16:35,362 --> 00:16:37,162
to call up and manipulate.

353
00:16:37,164 --> 00:16:40,432
Once you're logged in,
you can't log yourself out.

354
00:16:40,501 --> 00:16:42,100
( All gasp )

355
00:16:42,169 --> 00:16:44,036
Lisbeth: The only way
for you to log out

356
00:16:44,104 --> 00:16:46,505
is by dying in there.

357
00:16:46,573 --> 00:16:50,175
That brings me to another issue
you all need to know about.

358
00:16:50,244 --> 00:16:53,512
The Underworld doesn't have
a pain absorber function.

359
00:16:53,580 --> 00:16:55,113
( All gasping )

360
00:16:55,182 --> 00:16:58,183
If you take enough damage
to drop your h.P. To zero,

361
00:16:58,252 --> 00:17:00,452
you'll experience
loads of virtual pain.

362
00:17:00,521 --> 00:17:02,120
( All murmuring )

363
00:17:02,189 --> 00:17:03,422
Lisbeth: And finally...

364
00:17:05,125 --> 00:17:07,192
The Underworld's
in a chaotic state right now,

365
00:17:07,261 --> 00:17:09,528
and the devs
can't fully operate it,

366
00:17:09,596 --> 00:17:12,197
so once you convert
your character data

367
00:17:12,199 --> 00:17:14,799
to the Underworld,
there's no guarantee

368
00:17:14,801 --> 00:17:16,668
you'll be able
to convert it back.

369
00:17:16,737 --> 00:17:19,071
And worse, if you die there,

370
00:17:19,139 --> 00:17:22,407
there's a good chance you might
lose your character forever.

371
00:17:22,409 --> 00:17:23,408
Player: Did I hear her right?

372
00:17:23,410 --> 00:17:24,409
Player 2: How can she ask that?

373
00:17:24,411 --> 00:17:25,544
Player 3: Hard pass.

374
00:17:25,612 --> 00:17:27,345
Player 4: Yeah,
what's the point?

375
00:17:27,414 --> 00:17:28,947
Player 5: What a load of crap!

376
00:17:29,015 --> 00:17:31,349
If we help
and lose our characters,

377
00:17:31,418 --> 00:17:33,085
are you gonna
reimburse us for 'em?

378
00:17:33,153 --> 00:17:35,353
Or is this a trick
to weaken the tribes

379
00:17:35,422 --> 00:17:36,354
so you can take over!

380
00:17:36,423 --> 00:17:37,956
Klein: Hey!

381
00:17:38,024 --> 00:17:39,157
Lisbeth: You're wrong.

382
00:17:39,226 --> 00:17:40,492
We're not tricking you!

383
00:17:40,561 --> 00:17:42,094
( All murmuring )

384
00:17:42,162 --> 00:17:43,362
Lisbeth: We know
how hard you worked

385
00:17:43,430 --> 00:17:45,029
to build your characters up,

386
00:17:45,099 --> 00:17:48,300
and no amount of money
can replace their loss.

387
00:17:48,368 --> 00:17:50,168
We're not asking this lightly.

388
00:17:50,237 --> 00:17:52,036
We're begging you to help us.

389
00:17:52,106 --> 00:17:55,107
Right now, our friends are
fighting the American players

390
00:17:55,175 --> 00:17:56,775
alongside the underworlders,

391
00:17:56,843 --> 00:17:59,444
but they're outnumbered,
and they need reinforcements!

392
00:17:59,513 --> 00:18:01,446
Player 5: You're all
"s.A.O." Survivors,

393
00:18:01,515 --> 00:18:04,182
so you should be tough enough
to deal with it!

394
00:18:04,251 --> 00:18:06,651
Screw your sob story!
You think you're all that,

395
00:18:06,653 --> 00:18:08,320
just 'cause
you were in that game!

396
00:18:08,388 --> 00:18:10,722
Well, here's your chance
to prove how bad-ass you are!

397
00:18:10,791 --> 00:18:12,257
Player 6: Why should we care

398
00:18:12,259 --> 00:18:14,259
about hijackers
or a.I.S with souls?

399
00:18:14,261 --> 00:18:16,194
Player 7: Don't bring
this real-life crap

400
00:18:16,263 --> 00:18:18,196
into our game
and expect us to help!

401
00:18:18,265 --> 00:18:20,399
Player 8: You and
the rest of your "s.A.O." Club

402
00:18:20,467 --> 00:18:21,666
can deal with it!

403
00:18:21,668 --> 00:18:23,201
Player 5:
Go save the day again,

404
00:18:23,270 --> 00:18:24,536
you stuck-up jerks!

405
00:18:24,605 --> 00:18:25,637
( Players yelling )

406
00:18:31,211 --> 00:18:33,412
Lisbeth: It didn't work.

407
00:18:33,480 --> 00:18:36,348
No matter what I say,
they don't care.

408
00:18:37,551 --> 00:18:39,385
¶

409
00:18:55,502 --> 00:18:56,568
( Sighs )

410
00:19:02,709 --> 00:19:04,709
( Crowd muttering )

411
00:19:04,711 --> 00:19:06,111
( Lisbeth chuckles )

412
00:19:07,381 --> 00:19:08,513
You're right!

413
00:19:08,515 --> 00:19:10,449
This is a real-life problem!

414
00:19:12,252 --> 00:19:14,052
And as for us survivors,

415
00:19:14,121 --> 00:19:15,854
yeah, some of us
do blur the line

416
00:19:15,922 --> 00:19:18,390
between the real world
and the virtual,

417
00:19:18,459 --> 00:19:22,727
but we don't think we're tougher
or better than anyone here.

418
00:19:22,729 --> 00:19:24,529
None of us think we're heroes!

419
00:19:24,598 --> 00:19:26,131
Me and Silica,

420
00:19:26,200 --> 00:19:30,068
she and I go to a special school
for survivors.

421
00:19:30,137 --> 00:19:32,471
Once a month, the students
have to go to counseling

422
00:19:32,539 --> 00:19:35,474
'cause of the trauma
we still deal with.

423
00:19:35,542 --> 00:19:38,543
They ask us painful questions.

424
00:19:38,612 --> 00:19:40,879
They make some of the kids
take medication,

425
00:19:40,947 --> 00:19:43,215
even though it makes 'em sick.

426
00:19:43,283 --> 00:19:45,617
And the government,
they're afraid of us,

427
00:19:45,686 --> 00:19:48,953
so they monitor us like we're
a bunch of criminals!

428
00:19:48,955 --> 00:19:52,691
The truth is it's not just us
at the returnee school

429
00:19:52,759 --> 00:19:54,093
they're suspicious of.

430
00:19:55,295 --> 00:19:57,629
It's all vrmmo players.

431
00:19:57,698 --> 00:20:00,699
They think we're all
a bunch of deadbeats,

432
00:20:00,767 --> 00:20:04,302
losers dragging society down,

433
00:20:04,371 --> 00:20:08,173
cowards who don't pay taxes
and can't face reality.

434
00:20:08,242 --> 00:20:10,575
People are saying
we need the draft back,

435
00:20:10,644 --> 00:20:13,712
to force us to enlist, 'cause
at least we can be useful there.

436
00:20:13,780 --> 00:20:15,914
And even though
they think that about us,

437
00:20:15,982 --> 00:20:17,249
you know what I believe?

438
00:20:17,317 --> 00:20:19,718
That this here...

439
00:20:19,786 --> 00:20:21,153
This is reality.

440
00:20:22,589 --> 00:20:24,256
( Singing in Japanese )

441
00:20:24,324 --> 00:20:28,793
This world and all the other
virtual worlds connected to it,

442
00:20:28,863 --> 00:20:29,928
they're real.

443
00:20:29,996 --> 00:20:32,264
They're not just games we play.

444
00:20:32,332 --> 00:20:35,400
Here in v.R.,
I have a real life,

445
00:20:35,402 --> 00:20:36,869
and I have real friends.

446
00:20:36,937 --> 00:20:39,804
I laugh, and I cry,
and I feel real feelings,

447
00:20:39,806 --> 00:20:41,740
the same as offline!

448
00:20:41,808 --> 00:20:43,408
Isn't it like that for you?!

449
00:20:43,410 --> 00:20:45,744
We pour our hearts and souls
into this world,

450
00:20:45,812 --> 00:20:48,280
because it's different
from what we got out there!

451
00:20:48,348 --> 00:20:51,015
But if it's all
just a stupid game,

452
00:20:51,085 --> 00:20:54,352
if everything we've been through
and felt here is fake,

453
00:20:54,421 --> 00:20:57,021
if so, then in the end,

454
00:20:57,091 --> 00:20:59,291
what is real for us?!

455
00:20:59,359 --> 00:21:02,427
( Crying )

456
00:21:02,429 --> 00:21:05,363
All the worlds we've grown
fused together.

457
00:21:05,432 --> 00:21:07,766
They're as thick and tall
as the world tree.

458
00:21:07,834 --> 00:21:09,301
And from them...

459
00:21:09,369 --> 00:21:13,371
From them, the Underworld
started to bloom.

460
00:21:13,440 --> 00:21:15,174
I want to protect it.

461
00:21:16,443 --> 00:21:18,310
So please,

462
00:21:18,378 --> 00:21:20,579
please...

463
00:21:20,647 --> 00:21:21,513
Help us.

464
00:21:55,415 --> 00:21:56,414
( Blade slashes )

465
00:21:56,483 --> 00:21:58,750
( Pugilists scream )

466
00:21:58,819 --> 00:22:00,685
Bercouli: Don't stop!
Cut the next one!

467
00:22:00,754 --> 00:22:02,287
( Hooves pounding )

468
00:22:05,091 --> 00:22:06,090
( Asuna gasps )

469
00:22:06,092 --> 00:22:07,893
( Energy pulsing )

470
00:22:12,967 --> 00:22:14,233
( Bercouli gasps )

471
00:22:15,636 --> 00:22:16,835
( Asuna gasps )

472
00:22:20,775 --> 00:22:22,708
¶

473
00:22:34,655 --> 00:22:36,120
( Gabriel chuckles )

474
00:22:36,122 --> 00:22:37,923
( Red Knights yelling )

